This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of single image super-resolution, which is a common problem in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes an enhanced deep super-resolution network (EDSR) using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNN), which is a popular technique in computer vision research. 

The paper also discusses the use of residual learning techniques, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. 

Furthermore, the proposed multi-scale deep super-resolution system (MDSR) involves the reconstruction of high-resolution images of different upscaling factors, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper mentions the training procedure and stabilization of the model, which could be related to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
